text: Botniavasan is a cross-country skiing event held around Vörå in Finland. The event was first held in 2006. The event is held every year in February. The first time the event was first held was in 2006. The main race is 50 kilometers long. The event has been named after Vasaloppet in Sweden. == References == ==Other websites== *official webstie Category:2006 establishments in Europe Category:Skiing in Finland Category:2000s establishments in Finland
